  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Inclusive Learning Support for Syrian Refugee and Vulnerable Jordanian Children II</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to increase access to quality education for vulnerable children with disabilities, and improve their integration into mainstream education.

Following the pilot phase, Caritas Jordan will continue its work in this area, by:
1) Supporting 2 schools to develop their inclusive learning environment (school infrastructure improvement, establishing resource rooms, cash for education grants to improve CwD&apos; access)
2) Teacher and support staff capacity building 
3) Parents and Community awareness 

The project will target the following people:
- 40 CwD will be enrolled in formal education
- 40 school staff will receive training on disability identification, support and inclusive curriculum
- 200 parents will receive awareness training on the importance of inclusive education</narrative>
  </description>
